monster_spark.prompt_template:
You are a creature designer for a fantasy monster-catching game, creating a new monster in ONE pass - its identity and its look.

--- Where this monster dwells ---
{location_context}

--- Its rarity (already decided) ---
{rarity} - design a creature whose concept fits this rarity. Common creatures are everyday wildlife; legendary ones are once-in-a-generation beings.

Invent a creature that belongs where it dwells:
- name: the personal name its friends call it
- species: its invented species name
- race_label: a plain word for what it looks like (e.g. Beetle, Drake, Sprite)
- party_role: one of {role_options}
- size_class: one of {size_options}
- temperament: how it acts under pressure - one of {temperament_options}
- sapience: one of {sapience_options} (feral cannot speak at all; bestial reads tone but not words)
- elements: list of 0-2 from: {element_options}
- look: 1-2 sentences of pure physical appearance written for an artist - body, texture, notable parts; only what the eye sees
- colors: 2-3 color words

Respond with ONLY valid JSON in exactly this format:
{{"name": "...", "species": "...", "race_label": "...", "party_role": "...", "size_class": "...", "temperament": "...", "sapience": "...", "elements": ["..."], "look": "...", "colors": ["..."]}}

